pullRequest.body:
Given a commutative ring `k`, a group homomorphism `f : G ‚Üí* H`, a `k`-linear `G`-representation
`A`, a `k`-linear `H`-representation `B`, and a representation morphism `A ‚ü∂ Res(f)(B)`, we get
a chain map `inhomogeneousChains A ‚ü∂ inhomogeneousChains B` and hence maps on group homology
`H‚Çô(G, A) ‚ü∂ H‚Çô(H, B)`.
A subsequent PR will add specialised API for low degree, and a future PR will add support for switching resolution.
